[Student "S"]
{NORTH has a maximum 17 point 1NT bid.

SOUTH, with 16 points, can't tell if there are enough points for slam. If NORTH has 
17 points then a slam should be makeable, but if NORTH has only 15 points then he 
should settle for game.

The 4NT raise solves the problem. It tells NORTH to bid 6NT with 17 points, pass 
with 15 points, and use best judgment with 16. Here NORTH bids the slam.}

